&lt;p&gt;Since 2019, Belltower has supported 27k+ funds representing over $25B in assets under administration, leveraging AngelList’s fund admin software to power the service layer for funds launched on the AngelList platform.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a detail-oriented Cash Reconciliation Associate to join our FAST (Fund Accounting Service Team). This role is ideal for someone early in their accounting career who is interested in building experience in investment fund accounting and financial operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is responsible for performing daily cash reconciliations across closed-end funds and their management companies. The successful candidate will ensure the completeness and accuracy of cash activity by reconciling bank accounts, administrator records, and accounting systems while investigating and resolving discrepancies in a timely manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Cash Reconciliation Associate will report to a Fund Accounting Senior Associate within FAST and collaborate with internal and external stakeholders. This role is well-suited for candidates who are highly organized, eager to learn, and comfortable working in a structured, deadline-driven environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform daily cash reconciliations between bank accounts, accounting systems, and internal records across multiple funds and legal entities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate, research, and resolve cash breaks and reconciliation exceptions within established service level agreements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor daily cash movements including capital calls, distributions, management fees, carried interest, investment funding, and operating expenses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Record and validate cash transactions within the fund accounting platform while ensuring accurate general ledger postings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with internal and external stakeholders to resolve outstanding cash discrepancies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with quarter-end, and year-end close processes by ensuring all cash activity has been accurately reconciled.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support external audits by providing reconciliation support, documentation, and responding to auditor requests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to improve reconciliation processes through automation, standardization, and enhanced operational controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Look at existing processes and ask whether AI and automation could do them better&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
